{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":657,"text":"Some years ago, I set out to try to understand"},{"time":3159,"text":"if there was a possibility to develop biofuels"},{"time":5887,"text":"on a scale that would actually compete with fossil fuels"},{"time":10589,"text":"but not compete with agriculture for water,"},{"time":14273,"text":"fertilizer or land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16711,"text":"So here's what I came up with."},{"time":18241,"text":"Imagine that we build an enclosure where we put it"},{"time":19849,"text":"just underwater, and we fill it with wastewater"},{"time":22127,"text":"and some form of microalgae that produces oil,"},{"time":25255,"text":"and we make it out of some kind of flexible material"},{"time":27415,"text":"that moves with waves underwater,"},{"time":29487,"text":"and the system that we're going to build, of course,"},{"time":31527,"text":"will use solar energy to grow the algae,"},{"time":33847,"text":"and they use CO2, which is good,"},{"time":36058,"text":"and they produce oxygen as they grow."},{"time":38423,"text":"The algae that grow are in a container that"},{"time":42087,"text":"distributes the heat to the surrounding water,"},{"time":44879,"text":"and you can harvest them and make biofuels"},{"time":47143,"text":"and cosmetics and fertilizer and animal feed,"},{"time":49823,"text":"and of course you'd have to make a large area of this,"},{"time":52663,"text":"so you'd have to worry about other stakeholders"},{"time":55215,"text":"like fishermen and ships and such things, but hey,"},{"time":59407,"text":"we're talking about biofuels,"},{"time":61670,"text":"and we know the importance of potentially getting"},{"time":63872,"text":"an alternative liquid fuel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66351,"text":"Why are we talking about microalgae?"},{"time":69032,"text":"Here you see a graph showing you the different types"},{"time":72719,"text":"of crops that are being considered for making biofuels,"},{"time":76571,"text":"so you can see some things like soybean,"},{"time":79134,"text":"which makes 50 gallons per acre per year,"},{"time":81451,"text":"or sunflower or canola or jatropha or palm, and that"},{"time":86508,"text":"tall graph there shows what microalgae can contribute."},{"time":91002,"text":"That is to say, microalgae contributes between 2,000"},{"time":93533,"text":"and 5,000 gallons per acre per year,"},{"time":96325,"text":"compared to the 50 gallons per acre per year from soy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99677,"text":"So what are microalgae? Microalgae are micro --"},{"time":102941,"text":"that is, they're extremely small, as you can see here"},{"time":105389,"text":"a picture of those single-celled organisms"},{"time":108357,"text":"compared to a human hair."},{"time":110667,"text":"Those small organisms have been around"},{"time":113493,"text":"for millions of years and there's thousands"},{"time":115533,"text":"of different species of microalgae in the world,"},{"time":117757,"text":"some of which are the fastest-growing plants on the planet,"},{"time":120781,"text":"and produce, as I just showed you, lots and lots of oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123973,"text":"Now, why do we want to do this offshore?"},{"time":127261,"text":"Well, the reason we're doing this offshore is because"},{"time":130109,"text":"if you look at our coastal cities, there isn't a choice,"},{"time":134705,"text":"because we're going to use waste water, as I suggested,"},{"time":137504,"text":"and if you look at where most of the waste water"},{"time":139415,"text":"treatment plants are, they're embedded in the cities."},{"time":142984,"text":"This is the city of San Francisco, which has 900 miles"},{"time":146667,"text":"of sewer pipes under the city already,"},{"time":149322,"text":"and it releases its waste water offshore."},{"time":153298,"text":"So different cities around the world treat their waste water"},{"time":157210,"text":"differently. Some cities process it."},{"time":159578,"text":"Some cities just release the water."},{"time":161224,"text":"But in all cases, the water that's released is"},{"time":163882,"text":"perfectly adequate for growing microalgae."},{"time":166842,"text":"So let's envision what the system might look like."},{"time":168507,"text":"We call it OMEGA, which is an acronym for"},{"time":170609,"text":"Offshore Membrane Enclosures for Growing Algae."},{"time":175040,"text":"At NASA, you have to have good acronyms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177592,"text":"So how does it work? I sort of showed you how it works already."},{"time":180435,"text":"We put waste water and some source of CO2"},{"time":184155,"text":"into our floating structure,"},{"time":187202,"text":"and the waste water provides nutrients for the algae to grow,"},{"time":190843,"text":"and they sequester CO2 that would otherwise go off"},{"time":193561,"text":"into the atmosphere as a greenhouse gas."},{"time":196171,"text":"They of course use solar energy to grow,"},{"time":198499,"text":"and the wave energy on the surface provides energy"},{"time":201050,"text":"for mixing the algae, and the temperature"},{"time":203354,"text":"is controlled by the surrounding water temperature."},{"time":205914,"text":"The algae that grow produce oxygen, as I've mentioned,"},{"time":209268,"text":"and they also produce biofuels and fertilizer and food and"},{"time":212556,"text":"other bi-algal products of interest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215997,"text":"And the system is contained. What do I mean by that?"},{"time":219414,"text":"It's modular. Let's say something happens that's"},{"time":221540,"text":"totally unexpected to one of the modules."},{"time":223734,"text":"It leaks. It's struck by lightning."},{"time":225933,"text":"The waste water that leaks out is water that already now"},{"time":228542,"text":"goes into that coastal environment, and"},{"time":230930,"text":"the algae that leak out are biodegradable,"},{"time":233178,"text":"and because they're living in waste water,"},{"time":234264,"text":"they're fresh water algae, which means they can't"},{"time":237333,"text":"live in salt water, so they die."},{"time":239130,"text":"The plastic we'll build it out of is some kind of"},{"time":241290,"text":"well-known plastic that we have good experience with, and"},{"time":243922,"text":"we'll rebuild our modules to be able to reuse them again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248773,"text":"So we may be able to go beyond that when thinking about"},{"time":252345,"text":"this system that I'm showing you, and that is to say"},{"time":254822,"text":"we need to think in terms of the water, the fresh water,"},{"time":257656,"text":"which is also going to be an issue in the future,"},{"time":260022,"text":"and we're working on methods now"},{"time":261859,"text":"for recovering the waste water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264381,"text":"The other thing to consider is the structure itself."},{"time":267173,"text":"It provides a surface for things in the ocean,"},{"time":270224,"text":"and this surface, which is covered by seaweeds"},{"time":273467,"text":"and other organisms in the ocean,"},{"time":275961,"text":"will become enhanced marine habitat"},{"time":279948,"text":"so it increases biodiversity."},{"time":281611,"text":"And finally, because it's an offshore structure,"},{"time":283611,"text":"we can think in terms of how it might contribute"},{"time":286513,"text":"to an aquaculture activity offshore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290267,"text":"So you're probably thinking, \"Gee, this sounds"},{"time":291856,"text":"like a good idea. What can we do to try to see if it's real?\""},{"time":296427,"text":"Well, I set up laboratories in Santa Cruz"},{"time":300242,"text":"at the California Fish and Game facility,"},{"time":303404,"text":"and that facility allowed us to have big seawater tanks"},{"time":306453,"text":"to test some of these ideas."},{"time":308176,"text":"We also set up experiments in San Francisco"},{"time":310798,"text":"at one of the three waste water treatment plants,"},{"time":313629,"text":"again a facility to test ideas."},{"time":316125,"text":"And finally, we wanted to see where we could look at"},{"time":319429,"text":"what the impact of this structure would be"},{"time":322133,"text":"in the marine environment, and we set up a field site"},{"time":325790,"text":"at a place called Moss Landing Marine Lab"},{"time":328253,"text":"in Monterey Bay, where we worked in a harbor"},{"time":330613,"text":"to see what impact this would have on marine organisms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335459,"text":"The laboratory that we set up in Santa Cruz was our skunkworks."},{"time":338549,"text":"It was a place where we were growing algae"},{"time":341447,"text":"and welding plastic and building tools"},{"time":344112,"text":"and making a lot of mistakes,"},{"time":345635,"text":"or, as Edison said, we were"},{"time":347566,"text":"finding the 10,000 ways that the system wouldn't work."},{"time":351016,"text":"Now, we grew algae in waste water, and we built tools"},{"time":355262,"text":"that allowed us to get into the lives of algae"},{"time":358694,"text":"so that we could monitor the way they grow,"},{"time":360416,"text":"what makes them happy, how do we make sure that"},{"time":363118,"text":"we're going to have a culture that will survive and thrive."},{"time":367020,"text":"So the most important feature that we needed to develop were these"},{"time":370109,"text":"so-called photobioreactors, or PBRs."},{"time":372837,"text":"These were the structures that would be floating at the"},{"time":374180,"text":"surface made out of some inexpensive plastic material"},{"time":377605,"text":"that'll allow the algae to grow, and we had built lots and lots"},{"time":380262,"text":"of designs, most of which were horrible failures,"},{"time":383391,"text":"and when we finally got to a design that worked,"},{"time":385726,"text":"at about 30 gallons, we scaled it up"},{"time":388013,"text":"to 450 gallons in San Francisco."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391629,"text":"So let me show you how the system works."},{"time":393823,"text":"We basically take waste water with algae of our choice in it,"},{"time":397535,"text":"and we circulate it through this floating structure,"},{"time":400241,"text":"this tubular, flexible plastic structure,"},{"time":402973,"text":"and it circulates through this thing,"},{"time":404466,"text":"and there's sunlight of course, it's at the surface,"},{"time":407178,"text":"and the algae grow on the nutrients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409583,"text":"But this is a bit like putting your head in a plastic bag."},{"time":412005,"text":"The algae are not going to suffocate because of CO2,"},{"time":415262,"text":"as we would."},{"time":416101,"text":"They suffocate because they produce oxygen, and they"},{"time":418760,"text":"don't really suffocate, but the oxygen that they produce"},{"time":420936,"text":"is problematic, and they use up all the CO2."},{"time":424040,"text":"So the next thing we had to figure out was how we could"},{"time":426472,"text":"remove the oxygen, which we did by building this column"},{"time":429701,"text":"which circulated some of the water,"},{"time":431178,"text":"and put back CO2, which we did by bubbling the system"},{"time":434548,"text":"before we recirculated the water."},{"time":437000,"text":"And what you see here is the prototype,"},{"time":438704,"text":"which was the first attempt at building this type of column."},{"time":442502,"text":"The larger column that we then installed in San Francisco"},{"time":444942,"text":"in the installed system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446570,"text":"So the column actually had another very nice feature,"},{"time":449968,"text":"and that is the algae settle in the column,"},{"time":453085,"text":"and this allowed us to accumulate the algal biomass"},{"time":456659,"text":"in a context where we could easily harvest it."},{"time":459626,"text":"So we would remove the algaes that concentrated"},{"time":462401,"text":"in the bottom of this column, and then we could"},{"time":464969,"text":"harvest that by a procedure where you float the algae"},{"time":468792,"text":"to the surface and can skim it off with a net."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472688,"text":"So we wanted to also investigate what would be the impact"},{"time":476325,"text":"of this system in the marine environment,"},{"time":479256,"text":"and I mentioned we set up this experiment at a field site"},{"time":482736,"text":"in Moss Landing Marine Lab."},{"time":484976,"text":"Well, we found of course that this material became"},{"time":487816,"text":"overgrown with algae, and we needed then to develop"},{"time":490728,"text":"a cleaning procedure, and we also looked at how"},{"time":493136,"text":"seabirds and marine mammals interacted, and in fact you"},{"time":496073,"text":"see here a sea otter that found this incredibly interesting,"},{"time":499096,"text":"and would periodically work its way across this little"},{"time":502200,"text":"floating water bed, and we wanted to hire this guy"},{"time":505088,"text":"or train him to be able to clean the surface"},{"time":507177,"text":"of these things, but that's for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509584,"text":"Now really what we were doing,"},{"time":510905,"text":"we were working in four areas."},{"time":512677,"text":"Our research covered the biology of the system,"},{"time":515560,"text":"which included studying the way algae grew,"},{"time":517728,"text":"but also what eats the algae, and what kills the algae."},{"time":521377,"text":"We did engineering to understand what we would need"},{"time":523556,"text":"to be able to do to build this structure,"},{"time":525849,"text":"not only on the small scale, but how we would build it"},{"time":528552,"text":"on this enormous scale that will ultimately be required."},{"time":531868,"text":"I mentioned we looked at birds and marine mammals"},{"time":535068,"text":"and looked at basically the environmental impact"},{"time":537597,"text":"of the system, and finally we looked at the economics,"},{"time":540748,"text":"and what I mean by economics is,"},{"time":542395,"text":"what is the energy required to run the system?"},{"time":545500,"text":"Do you get more energy out of the system"},{"time":546922,"text":"than you have to put into the system"},{"time":548503,"text":"to be able to make the system run?"},{"time":550516,"text":"And what about operating costs?"},{"time":552262,"text":"And what about capital costs?"},{"time":554320,"text":"And what about, just, the whole economic structure?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558478,"text":"So let me tell you that it's not going to be easy,"},{"time":561196,"text":"and there's lots more work to do in all four"},{"time":563756,"text":"of those areas to be able to really make the system work."},{"time":567348,"text":"But we don't have a lot of time, and I'd like to show you"},{"time":570268,"text":"the artist's conception of how this system might look"},{"time":573770,"text":"if we find ourselves in a protected bay"},{"time":576450,"text":"somewhere in the world, and we have in the background"},{"time":579634,"text":"in this image, the waste water treatment plant"},{"time":582402,"text":"and a source of flue gas for the CO2,"},{"time":585275,"text":"but when you do the economics of this system,"},{"time":588010,"text":"you find that in fact it will be difficult to make it work."},{"time":591082,"text":"Unless you look at the system as a way to treat waste water,"},{"time":595652,"text":"sequester carbon, and potentially for photovoltaic panels"},{"time":599380,"text":"or wave energy or even wind energy,"},{"time":602860,"text":"and if you start thinking in terms of"},{"time":604131,"text":"integrating all of these different activities,"},{"time":607172,"text":"you could also include in such a facility aquaculture."},{"time":611819,"text":"So we would have under this system a shellfish aquaculture"},{"time":614747,"text":"where we're growing mussels or scallops."},{"time":616841,"text":"We'd be growing oysters and things"},{"time":619833,"text":"that would be producing high value products and food,"},{"time":622671,"text":"and this would be a market driver as we build the system"},{"time":625441,"text":"to larger and larger scales so that it becomes, ultimately,"},{"time":628755,"text":"competitive with the idea of doing it for fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634556,"text":"So there's always a big question that comes up,"},{"time":637253,"text":"because plastic in the ocean has got a really bad reputation"},{"time":640597,"text":"right now, and so we've been thinking cradle to cradle."},{"time":643586,"text":"What are we going to do with all this plastic that we're"},{"time":646303,"text":"going to need to use in our marine environment?"},{"time":649044,"text":"Well, I don't know if you know about this,"},{"time":650562,"text":"but in California, there's a huge amount of plastic"},{"time":653324,"text":"that's used in fields right now as plastic mulch,"},{"time":656669,"text":"and this is plastic that's making these tiny little greenhouses"},{"time":659893,"text":"right along the surface of the soil, and this provides"},{"time":662644,"text":"warming the soil to increase the growing season,"},{"time":665902,"text":"it allows us to control weeds,"},{"time":668445,"text":"and, of course, it makes the watering much more efficient."},{"time":672037,"text":"So the OMEGA system will be part"},{"time":674350,"text":"of this type of an outcome, and that when we're finished"},{"time":677429,"text":"using it in the marine environment, we'll be using it,"},{"time":680118,"text":"hopefully, on fields."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682671,"text":"Where are we going to put this,"},{"time":683991,"text":"and what will it look like offshore?"},{"time":686502,"text":"Here's an image of what we could do in San Francisco Bay."},{"time":689493,"text":"San Francisco produces 65 million gallons a day"},{"time":692173,"text":"of waste water. If we imagine a five-day retention time"},{"time":694933,"text":"for this system, we'd need 325 million gallons"},{"time":697302,"text":"to accomodate, and that would be about 1,280 acres"},{"time":701328,"text":"of these OMEGA modules floating in San Francisco Bay."},{"time":704947,"text":"Well, that's less than one percent"},{"time":706741,"text":"of the surface area of the bay."},{"time":708492,"text":"It would produce, at 2,000 gallons per acre per year,"},{"time":712234,"text":"it would produce over 2 million gallons of fuel,"},{"time":715230,"text":"which is about 20 percent of the biodiesel,"},{"time":717430,"text":"or of the diesel that would be required in San Francisco,"},{"time":720438,"text":"and that's without doing anything about efficiency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723628,"text":"Where else could we potentially put this system?"},{"time":726598,"text":"There's lots of possibilities."},{"time":729498,"text":"There's, of course, San Francisco Bay, as I mentioned."},{"time":731550,"text":"San Diego Bay is another example,"},{"time":733366,"text":"Mobile Bay or Chesapeake Bay, but the reality is,"},{"time":736279,"text":"as sea level rises, there's going to be lots and lots"},{"time":738371,"text":"of new opportunities to consider. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":742278,"text":"So what I'm telling you about is a system"},{"time":745846,"text":"of integrated activities."},{"time":749478,"text":"Biofuels production is integrated with alternative energy"},{"time":752088,"text":"is integrated with aquaculture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754890,"text":"I set out to find a pathway"},{"time":758814,"text":"to innovative production of sustainable biofuels,"},{"time":764460,"text":"and en route I discovered that what's really required"},{"time":767708,"text":"for sustainability is integration more than innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774985,"text":"Long term, I have great faith"},{"time":778415,"text":"in our collective and connected ingenuity."},{"time":783560,"text":"I think there is almost no limit to what we can accomplish"},{"time":787876,"text":"if we are radically open"},{"time":790078,"text":"and we don't care who gets the credit."},{"time":793808,"text":"Sustainable solutions for our future problems"},{"time":798024,"text":"are going to be diverse"},{"time":800424,"text":"and are going to be many."},{"time":802889,"text":"I think we need to consider everything,"},{"time":805680,"text":"everything from alpha to OMEGA."},{"time":808712,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":811592,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":817347,"text":"Chris Anderson: Just a quick question for you, Jonathan."},{"time":820559,"text":"Can this project continue to move forward within"},{"time":822767,"text":"NASA or do you need some very ambitious"},{"time":826732,"text":"green energy fund to come and take it by the throat?"},{"time":830808,"text":"Jonathan Trent: So it's really gotten to a stage now"},{"time":832111,"text":"in NASA where they would like to spin it out into something"},{"time":835125,"text":"which would go offshore, and there are a lot of issues"},{"time":837516,"text":"with doing it in the United States because of limited"},{"time":839743,"text":"permitting issues and the time required to get permits"},{"time":842237,"text":"to do things offshore."},{"time":843751,"text":"It really requires, at this point, people on the outside,"},{"time":846549,"text":"and we're being radically open with this technology"},{"time":848853,"text":"in which we're going to launch it out there"},{"time":850565,"text":"for anybody and everybody who's interested"},{"time":852841,"text":"to take it on and try to make it real."},{"time":854681,"text":"CA: So that's interesting. You're not patenting it."},{"time":857158,"text":"You're publishing it."},{"time":858833,"text":"JT: Absolutely."},{"time":859596,"text":"CA: All right. Thank you so much."},{"time":861487,"text":"JT: Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}